{{Year in Sri Lanka|1988}}

The following lists events that happened during '''[[1988]] in [[Sri Lanka]]'''.

==Incumbents==
*[[President of Sri Lanka|President]]: [[J. R. Jayewardene]]

==Events==
* In the north and east, soldiers of the Indian Peace Keeping Force battled Tamil Tiger rebels.<ref>{{cite web|author=David Brewster|url= https://www.academia.edu/7992855/Extract_from_Indias_Ocean_-_the_lead_up_to_Indias_1987_intervention_in_Sri_Lanka |title=India’s Ocean: the Story of India’s Bid for Regional Leadership. Retrieved 13 August 2014}}</ref>
* In the south, government death squads are engaged with equally brutal militants of the radical [[Janatha Vimukthi Peramuna|JVP]] party.
* Sri Lanka starts their 9th parliamentary elections.

